SUMMARY:Partition: An Improvised Severance Parody
DESCRIPTION:Th\, Fri & Sat 7:30pm at West of Lenin Theatre \nWhat happens when your work self and your real self stop agreeing? \nPartition is an improvised workplace dramedy inspired by the eerie tone of Severance. Each performance follows characters living divided lives\, one version of themselves at work and another outside of it. As those identities begin to blur\, the results are funny\, unsettling\, and deeply human. \nThis is not a mystery to be solved. It is an experience to inhabit. Expect uneasy laughter\, unexpected connections\, and moments that linger long after the show ends. \nLeave your memories at the door. Pick them up on your way out.
URL:https://myballard.com/event/partition-an-improvised-severance-parody/
LOCATION:West of Lenin\, 203 N 36th St #204\, Seattle\, WA\, 98103\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://myballard.com/wp-content/uploads/Seattle-Mag-1.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Jet City Improv":MAILTO:reservations@jetcityimprov.org
END:VEVENT
