SUMMARY:Crochet Class: Book Cover Granny Squares
DESCRIPTION:While this class is beginner-friendly\, knowing the basics like a slip knot\, single crochet\, and double crochet will be necessary for this project. If you would like to join and don’t have these skills yet check out my beginner crochet class at Swoon City or find some good tutorials on YouTube. I taught myself to crochet before the Internet existed and have all the faith you can learn too! \nWe will make a classic granny square in this class\, but there are many variations of granny squares. Granny squares can create bags\, blankets\, sweaters\, and more! We will focus on making granny squares that resemble book covers. You can use the cover colors or even replicate the parts of the cover design! \nThis class will include all the colors necessary to create your book-themed granny square\, a guide to making granny squares\, and a hook. Please provide a picture of the cover you are looking to create to info@swoon.city after booking
URL:https://myballard.com/event/crochet-class-book-cover-granny-squares/
LOCATION:Swoon City\, 1716 NW Market St\, Seattle\, WA\, 98107\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://myballard.com/wp-content/uploads/crochet.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Swoon City":MAILTO:info@swoon.city
END:VEVENT
