SUMMARY:2026 Seattle Sister Cities Soup Sampling
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate International Women’s Day at the 2nd annual Seattle Sister Cities’ Soup Sampling\, sponsored by the Seattle Sister Cities Association in partnership with the National Nordic Museum. The Soup Sampling is a community event where volunteer cooks from 11 Seattle Sister Cities share popular international soups representing four continents. Guests need to bring only a smile and an interest in tasting new recipes and learning about diverse cultures. Please register for the event before March 1st; walk-in admission will not be available. \nThis is a cultural event that includes five soup tastings per entry. Donations of $10 per person are encouraged and benefit the nonprofit Seattle Sister Cities Association to support cultural\, educational\, and humanitarian programs. (When reserving tickets\, your donation will result in 1 admission ticket. Use the quantity selector to reserve tickets for additional attendees). From Seattle’s 20 sister cities\, the following will be represented at this event: Reykjavik\, Iceland; Bergen\, Norway; Pecs\, Hungary; Be’er Sheva\, Israel; Christchurch\, New Zealand; Mombasa\, Kenya; Sihanoukville\, Cambodia; Perugia\, Italy; Surabaya\, Indonesia; Hai Phong\, Vietnam; and Kobe\, Japan. \nAttendees are also encouraged to visit New Nordic: Cuisine\, Aesthetics and Place as well as other exhibits at the National Nordic Museum and will get 50% off admission on the day of this event
URL:https://myballard.com/event/2026-seattle-sister-cities-soup-sampling/
LOCATION:National Nordic Museum\, 2655 NW Market Street\, Seattle\, WA\, 98107\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://myballard.com/wp-content/uploads/Soup-Sampling-Eventbrite-2026-2160-x-1080-px.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Seattle Sister Cities":MAILTO:SoupEvent@SeattleSisterCities.org
END:VEVENT
