SUMMARY:Art Class: Nature Journaling & basics of making botanical Inks
DESCRIPTION:Pause and see the natural world more closely through nature journaling and botanical inks. In this gentle\, hands-on class\, you’ll learn the basics of making ink from flowers and use these plant-based pigments to start a nature journal. You’ll also learn how considerations like paper and additives can give you different and exciting colors. All materials are included and each participant will take home a small sketchbook that we make in class and a 15ml pot of handmade floral ink—an invitation to notice new growth\, returning light\, and the unfolding of spring.
URL:https://myballard.com/event/art-class-nature-journaling-basics-of-making-botanical-inks/
LOCATION:Swoon City\, 1716 NW Market St\, Seattle\, WA\, 98107\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://myballard.com/wp-content/uploads/Ink.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Swoon City":MAILTO:info@swoon.city
END:VEVENT
