SUMMARY:Spring Dance
DESCRIPTION:ARC Dance presents its annual Spring Dance performances featuring early dances from the 17th and 18th century re-created by Dance Historian\, Anna Mansbridge. The program also includes excerpts from the classic “La fille mal gardée”\, a charming comedic ballet choreographed by Artistic Director Marie Chong. The complete ballet will premiere on May 30\, 2026 at Shorewood Performing Arts Center. \nThis family-friendly performance takes the audience on a beautiful progression through dance history\, from early court dances to one of the oldest story ballets still being performed today.  \nMarch 21 and 22 at 4pm\nARC Performance Space in Ballard/Crown Hill\, 9250 14th Ave NW\nTickets available at arcdance.org
URL:https://myballard.com/event/spring-dance/
LOCATION:ARC Dance Space\, 9250 14th Avenue NW\, Seattle\, 98117\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://myballard.com/wp-content/uploads/Spring-Dance-ARC.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="ARC Dance Productions":MAILTO:info@arcdance.org
END:VEVENT
