SUMMARY:Ballard Bookworms Community Storytime
DESCRIPTION:Calling all bookworms! Ballard Preschool Co-op (BPC) is thrilled to present its FREE monthly Ballard Bookworms story time. Join BPC’s beloved Teacher Christine for a fun and engaging story time designed to spark a love of reading and build connections within our community. \nThis month our Special Guest is Emily Weissman (known online as Urb.Em.Sketches) a local urban sketcher\, author and illustrator. Emily’s watercolor paintings celebrate beloved neighborhood places that make Seattle extraordinary. She will be reading her children’s book\, My Home is With You\, a whimsical exploration of how home is not just a place\, but found in the hearts of those we love. \nBallard Bookworms is free and open to the public\, so be sure to invite your friends & neighbors! Recommended for ages 5 and under (older siblings welcome) \nThis program is organized by the Ballard Preschool Co-op and is held in a library branch meeting room. The Seattle Public Library does not sponsor or endorse this event.
URL:https://myballard.com/event/ballard-bookworms-community-storytime/
LOCATION:Greenwood Public Library\, 8016 Greenwood Ave N\,\, Seattle\, 98103\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://myballard.com/wp-content/uploads/BBW-for-Seattle-Child-Katie-at-GW-scaled.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Ballard Preschool Co-op":MAILTO:bpc.allschoolchair@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
