SUMMARY:Help Design the Alice Ball Park Sign
DESCRIPTION:Community members are invited to help shape a new 24” x 36” interpretive sign for Alice Ball Park. The sign will share the story of Alice Ball\, the Seattle-born chemist who developed the first effective treatment for Hansen’s disease. \nTake a 5–10 minute survey:\nhttps://forms.gle/tHyaCttEonz4yxjn8 \nOr attend a public open house:\n• Greenwood Library — March 30\, 3:30 PM \nAll ages welcome.
URL:https://myballard.com/event/help-design-the-alice-ball-park-sign/
LOCATION:Greenwood Public Library\, 8016 Greenwood Ave N\,\, Seattle\, 98103\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://myballard.com/wp-content/uploads/48719278746_5c0e5819b7_4k-scaled-e1696971139646-2000x800-1.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Phinney Neighborhood Asscociation":MAILTO:pna@phinneycenter.org
