SUMMARY:Macrame Class: Keychain Wristlet
DESCRIPTION:In this workshop with Angie Cooper of My Moon Macrame you will be taught the basic knotting techniques used in macrame. This class is great for beginners and intermediate levels. This project is designed to be altered to cater to students at any skill level. We provide craft supplies\, video tutorials and one-on-one guidance to help you create your macrame project. \nDuring this class you will learn to macrame a lanyard keychain. Your instructor\, Angie from My Moon Macrame will teach you the knots and provide step by step instructions to help you complete your project. We provide all craft supplies\, video tutorials and one-on-one guidance. This project is designed to cater to students at any skill level. You will go home with a completed macrame lanyard keychain and all the tools you need to continue your macrame journey at home. \nSupplies: \n4mm Oeko Tex Recycled Cotton Cord\nKey Ring\nScissors\nTape
URL:https://myballard.com/event/macrame-class-keychain-wristlet/
LOCATION:Swoon City\, 1716 NW Market St\, Seattle\, WA\, 98107\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://myballard.com/wp-content/uploads/Screenshot-2026-02-10-at-9.28.20-PM.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Swoon City":MAILTO:info@swoon.city
END:VEVENT
